Title: On the gauge-invariant operator $A^2_{\min}$ in Euclidean Yang-Mills  theories
Authors: M. A. L. Capri and D. Fiorentini and M. S. Guimaraes and B. W. Mintz and L. F. Palhares and S. P. Sorella
Abstract: We review our recent work on the gauge-invariant non-local dimension-two operator $A^2_{\rm min}$, whose minimization is defined along the gauge orbit. Albeit non-local, the operator $A^2_{\rm min}$ can be cast in local form through the introduction of an auxiliary Stueckelberg field. The whole procedure results into a local action which turns out to be renormalizable to all orders.
